<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Strategy for SH Words</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Weigh the S cost:</span> S is the best pluralizing tile. Only use it in SH words if you score 10+ more than adding S to an existing word for a parallel play.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">-ISH suffix is gold:</span> Add -ISH to adjectives for 6+ letter words (FOOLISH, REDDISH, SMALLISH). These often qualify for bingo bonuses when you already have the base word on the board.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">-SH endings are defensive:</span> Words ending in SH (CRUSH, TRASH, FLUSH) are difficult for opponents to extend, making them excellent board-control plays.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Place H on premiums:</span> H is worth 4 — target Double or Triple Letter Squares. SHRIMP with H on a TLS scores the H portion alone as 12.</p>
  </div>
</div>

